<div><h3>MKT 5407 - Services Marketing </h3>  <hr>Services now comprise a significant and increasing percentage of the US and global revenues for companies. This makes it critical to understand the unique differences in approaching market planning and marketing programs with services. This course is focused on exploring those differences, using current actual service brands and competitive situations. Students will have an opportunity to work in groups within each class to create service concepts, service development and positioning, value propositions, demand and process management, service quality and recovery, marketing strategies and media promotion campaigns.<br><br><strong>Prerequisites:</strong> <a href="preview_course_nopop.php?catoid=28&coid=93787" onclick="acalogPopup('preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93787&print', '3', 770, 530, 'yes');return false;" rel="remote /ajax/preview_course.php?catoid=28&coid=93787&display_options[location]=tooltip&show" id="tt3322" target="_blank">MKT 4400</a><span style="display: none !important">&#160;</span>Â or waiver.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Varies<br><br><div style="display: none; z-index: 1000;" class="tooltip for_tt3322"></div></div>		</td>
